# research-profile wiki — privacy-default .gitignore
#
# This wiki holds material that should not be committed by accident:
# unpublished ideas, embargoed results, peer reviews under referee
# privilege, frank collaborator notes, and grant applications.
#
# The defaults below err on the side of NOT committing. Review and
# adjust on first run. If you want something tracked, remove its line.

# Raw paper PDFs — most are copyrighted, almost never belong in git
raw/

# Peer reviews you wrote — referee privilege is permanent
reviews/

# Grant applications and funding plans — often agency-confidential
funding/

# Frank collaborator notes — written for your future memory, not for sharing
collaborators/

# CV-style exports — change frequently, regeneratable, no value in history
snapshots/

# Editor/OS junk
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Local-only overrides — anything you want to keep private even from your
# private remote. Use this for keys, drafts you are deeply uncertain about,
# or wiki experiments you do not want history for.
*.local.md
*.private.md

# OPTIONAL: uncomment if you want even ideas kept local-only
# ideas/promising/
# ideas/parked/
# ideas/killed/

# OPTIONAL: uncomment if you want failures kept local-only (they are
# usually safe to commit but the choice is yours)
# failures/

# OPTIONAL: uncomment if you do NOT want paper drafts in git
# papers/drafts/
# papers/rejected/
